                <h2>Common patterns</h2>
                
                <h3 class="h5 mt-4">Entity naming conventions</h3>
                <ul>
                    <li>Entities use Pascal case (e.g., <code>Risk</code>, <code>ActionSource</code>)</li>
                    <li>Properties use Pascal case (e.g., <code>Title</code>, <code>DueDate</code>)</li>
                    <li>Foreign keys include the entity name (e.g., <code>ObjectiveId</code>, <code>OwnerUserId</code>)</li>
                    <li>Navigation properties match the entity name (e.g., <code>Objective</code>, <code>OwnerUser</code>)</li>
                </ul>

                <h3 class="h5 mt-4">Status field conventions</h3>
                <p>Status fields use lowercase with underscores:</p>
                <ul>
                    <li>Risks: <code>new</code>, <code>open</code>, <code>treating</code>, <code>monitoring</code>, <code>closed</code></li>
                    <li>Issues: <code>open</code>, <code>in_progress</code>, <code>blocked</code>, <code>resolved</code>, <code>closed</code></li>
                    <li>Actions: <code>not_started</code>, <code>in_progress</code>, <code>blocked</code>, <code>done</code>, <code>cancelled</code></li>
                    <li>Milestones: <code>not_started</code>, <code>on_track</code>, <code>at_risk</code>, <code>delayed</code>, <code>complete</code>, <code>cancelled</code></li>
                </ul>

                <h3 class="h5 mt-4">DTOs and reporting projections</h3>
                <p>Compass avoids exposing Entity Framework tracking proxies via the API. Dedicated DTOs and LINQ projections shape the payloads instead:</p>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>Create/Update DTOs</strong> – <code>RiskCreateDto</code>, <code>RiskUpdateDto</code>, and <code>ActionCreateDto</code> validate inbound data, perform range checks, and control which fields can be changed.</li>
                    <li><strong>List projections</strong> – <code>RisksController</code> and <code>ActionsController</code> project to anonymous types that flatten lookup information (tier names, risk types, action sources) for lighter responses.</li>
                    <li><strong>Reporting view models</strong> – classes in <code>Models/DashboardViewModel.cs</code>, <code>PortfolioReportViewModel.cs</code>, and similar files aggregate pre-calculated metrics for dashboards without overloading the base entities.</li>
                </ul>
                <p class="small text-muted">If you extend the API, create a new DTO rather than posting raw entities. This keeps validation logic centralised and stops accidental exposure of internal-only fields such as audit metadata.</p>

